.TH LAMBOOT-INSPECT 1 "2026-04-22" "LamBoot 0.8.3" "LamBoot"
.SH NAME
lamboot-inspect \- parse LamBoot diagnostic artefacts and verify installation claims
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lamboot-inspect
.RB [ \-\-version ]
.I subcommand
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lamboot-inspect
reads the on-disk artefacts LamBoot writes to the EFI System Partition during
and after each boot, renders them for human or machine consumption, and
verifies that LamBoot's public claims are backed by real code paths.

The tool is strictly read-only: no subcommand modifies any file on the ESP or
any system state. Every subcommand auto-detects the ESP mount point (trying
.IR /boot/efi ", " /efi ", " /boot )
or accepts an explicit
.B \-\-path
override.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B trust-log
Parse
.I /loader/boot-trust.log
(JSON-lines per
.B SPEC-NATIVE-TRUST-CHAIN
§6) and render events. Supports
.BR text " (coloured, default), " json " (machine-readable), " timeline " (compact), and " stats " (aggregate counts)."
.RS
Options: \fB\-\-path\fR,
.BR \-\-format = \fItext\fR|\fIjson\fR|\fItimeline\fR|\fIstats\fR,
.BR \-\-event " " \fIevent_name\fR
(filter),
.B \-\-errors-only,
.B \-\-no-sha,
.B \-\-strict
(exit 4 on schema violations).
.RE
.TP
.B boot-log
Parse the human-readable boot log
.I /EFI/LamBoot/reports/boot.log
and render it with optional phase timing.
.RS
Options: \fB\-\-path\fR,
.BR \-\-level " " \fIDEBUG\fR|\fIINFO\fR|\fIWARN\fR|\fIERROR\fR,
.B \-\-errors-only,
.BR \-\-format = \fItext\fR|\fIjson\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B summary
One-screen overview of the last boot. Reads trust log, boot log, boot.json
report, and audit.log (whichever are present) and renders a condensed view
including the verify→load SHA-256 invariant check.
.TP
.B show \fIidentifier\fR
Show one event's full detail. The identifier may be a sequence number, an
event name (returns the first match), or an image path.
.TP
.B verify
Walk the SDS-4 §8.1 permitted-claims table and confirm each is backed by
code-path evidence in the current checkout. Returns exit code 0 if all
claims are substantiated, 5 otherwise.
.RS
Options: \fB\-\-repo\fR
.I path
(defaults to current directory),
.B \-\-verbose
(include SDS section references).
.RE
.TP
.B dump
Produce a diagnostic bundle (.tar.gz) containing every LamBoot artefact plus
system-context probes (uname, lsblk, blkid, efibootmgr, mokutil state) and
LamBoot-namespace EFI variables, each with a SHA-256. Intended for attaching
to bug reports.
.RS
Options:
.BR \-\-output " " \fIpath\fR,
.BR \-\-esp " " \fIpath\fR
(override ESP auto-detection),
.BR \-\-print-manifest .
.RE
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Usage error (unknown subcommand, bad argument).
.TP
.B 2
Source file unreadable (not found, permission denied).
.TP
.B 3
Parse error (log content malformed beyond recovery).
.TP
.B 4
Schema violation (\fB\-\-strict\fR; records parsed but fail SDS-4 §6 schema).
.TP
.B 5
Verification failed (claims not substantiated).
.TP
.B 6
Dump collection failed.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable ANSI colour output. Honoured on all subcommands.
.TP
.B LAMBOOT_DIAG_FORCE_COLOR
Set to
.I 1
to force colour output even when stdout is not a terminal. Useful for piping
into \fBless \-R\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /boot/efi/loader/boot-trust.log
Trust event log (JSON-lines, schema v2).
.TP
.I /boot/efi/EFI/LamBoot/reports/boot.log
Human-readable boot trace.
.TP
.I /boot/efi/EFI/LamBoot/reports/boot.json
Machine-readable last-boot report.
.TP
.I /boot/efi/EFI/LamBoot/reports/audit.log
Cumulative audit log across boots.
.TP
.I /boot/efi/EFI/LamBoot/policy.toml
Active boot policy.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lamboot-install (1),
.BR mokutil (1),
.BR efibootmgr (8),
.BR lsblk (8).
.PP
.B docs/specs/SPEC-NATIVE-TRUST-CHAIN.md
for the authoritative trust-chain and event-schema specification.
.SH AUTHOR
LamCo. Licensed MIT OR Apache-2.0.
.SH REPORTING BUGS
Run
.B lamboot-inspect dump
and attach the generated .tar.gz to
.UR https://github.com/lamco-admin/lamboot/issues
the issue tracker
.UE .
